The HER2 protein "favors the growth of several types of cancer," including breast, ovarian, lung and colorectal cancers, Berzofsky said.
A similar approach consisting of extracting immune cells from patients and “teaching” these cells how to treat cancer cells has worked in the treatment of one type of leukemia.
